<subSubSection id="30979FE42958865AEB1BED16669E3E5F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="variation">
<paragraph id="FBECDD5DBC69E60F199ECAFF7B5895EE" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Variation.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8657B5DF0B82B8B53EC8FFADCC4FA55C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Specimens from southern Taiwan possess a broader aedeagus and the broader endophallic sclerite near apex that is almost straight in lateral view.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="780AD280078093A0AE47C168A6BF5DD1" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="9EE410FC36A431C89318F87EED56107F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C95384719E33BAF5A6EED6AEBB885360" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Adults of 
<taxonomicName id="97659E47E44CF6822B399DBB3E4044C5" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rosaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. houjayi" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="houjayi">
<emphasis id="9EB4A6FB4356A5F07DF5CFDDF91D4C72" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. houjayi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. and 
<taxonomicName id="10D814269989B32367FC79A682BB2EAB" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rosaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. taiwana" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="taiwana">
<emphasis id="946715A7E0FA928F31A50E19E9A4B876" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. taiwana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kimoto are characterized by their partly green elytra lacking longitudinal ridges. 
<taxonomicName id="5217E47C575889DA5C57B3422F95D69E" authorityName="Lee &amp; Bezděk" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Ericaceae" genus="Pyrrhalta" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pyrrhalta houjayi" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="houjayi">
<emphasis id="A7FF7430B8D13C7BD84AEECAE266BA35" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Pyrrhalta houjayi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="2AA5E8CD05D3132FA4EFC613F124B4D0" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rosaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. taiwana" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="taiwana">
<emphasis id="256049BB2AC7D49D1FB4490BE22569B7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. taiwana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by presence of the wide brown band along the suture of the elytra, and more slender elytra (Figs 
<figureCitation id="ED07EF5D026992878079CB6631150A8E" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Habitus of Pyrrhalta gressitti Kimoto, P. houjayi sp. nov., and P. tahsiangi sp. nov. A P. gressitti, male, dorsal view B ditto, ventral view C ditto, lateral view D P. houjayi sp. nov., male, dorsal view E ditto, ventral view F ditto, lateral view G P. tahsiangi sp. nov., male, dorsal view H ditto, ventral view I ditto, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545535" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">5D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="7B56AA1D555E5EC968F09D02E8286217" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Field photographs of Pyrrhalta houjayi sp. nov. on host plant A young larvae feeding on tender shoots B host plant blooming and sprouting at the same time in Tahsuehshan (大雪山) C flower buds with holes caused by larvae D Larva found inside the flower buds E one larva feeding on pedicels F adults." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545539" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">9F</figureCitation>
), 1.8 
<normalizedToken id="8E4D3243851A9A2C6942137AC6C82911" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide (lacking brown band on elytra, and wider elytra (Figs 
<figureCitation id="E44C61CB0435F5A82B7EF4E4D5EC3113" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Habitus of Pyrrhalta taiwana Kimoto and P. viridipennis Kimoto A P. taiwana, male, dorsal view B ditto, ventral view C ditto, lateral view D P. viridipennis, male, dorsal view E ditto, ventral view F ditto, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545541" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">11A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="C62A55287D16C2121554F540775F870F" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Field photographs of Pyrrhalta taiwana Kimoto and P. viridipennis Kimoto on host plant A host plant for P. tahsiangi, Vaccinium randaiense B mature larva of P. taiwana C pupa of P. taiwana D adult of P. taiwana E Third-instar larva of P. viridipennis F adult of P. viridipennis." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545543" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">13D</figureCitation>
), 1.6 
<normalizedToken id="D311FB88373E2C6F1CD507CA98CDE23D" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide in 
<taxonomicName id="CED01C4A5FF74F50B8AB6956CE368874" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rosaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. taiwana" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="taiwana">
<emphasis id="C64CE236C7F1651E3252158F710EDD1E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. taiwana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); slender aedeagus, 7.4 
<normalizedToken id="8509B245EDF4C4A28DEC6CA21557917E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide, with apex curved to right (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="FAA42A8D025C4045F9813718AEBE5CE9" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta houjayi sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F spermatheca G abdominal ventrite V, female H abdominal ventrite V, male I gonocoxae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545538" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">8C</figureCitation>
) (broad aedeagus, 6.8 
<normalizedToken id="B89C1B90E9D46F92B236DAF360E5AB2D" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide, with tapering apex (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="5B100E645B8D3361E5387EB03B30E0A3" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta houjayi sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F spermatheca G gonocoxae H abdominal ventrite V, female I abdominal ventrite V, male." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545542" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">12C</figureCitation>
) in 
<taxonomicName id="4891B71B567C594598289F592A9D52CC" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rosaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. taiwana" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="taiwana">
<emphasis id="367DA556D2EF7DFAFFE8ACE1AFACB402" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. taiwana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); two endophallic slerites, primary endophallic sclerite with teeth at apex (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="84DE6B40AF6BCC2DADB5639A38CD33BF" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta houjayi sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F spermatheca G abdominal ventrite V, female H abdominal ventrite V, male I gonocoxae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545538" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">8C, D</figureCitation>
) (one endophallic sclerite slender, lacking teeth at apex (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="31529F308FFDA0715BC849EE2C9C5D41" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta houjayi sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F spermatheca G gonocoxae H abdominal ventrite V, female I abdominal ventrite V, male." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545542" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">12C, D</figureCitation>
) in 
<taxonomicName id="368D8BC32DF66CB039DBC991E88A9F25" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rosaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. taiwana" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="taiwana">
<emphasis id="C780921F0EFF15BB56D3296DDA51EA7C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. taiwana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F0CF3F89699961BA4A8F4356A07E3D6E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="host">
<paragraph id="15FFD6552F2D310CFAB953DEEF20605A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Host plants.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5F3C580A33B05F10D34F3467DF0D0E1B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Larvae and adults feed on leaves of 
<taxonomicName id="CC50C00164FE4000989487543E593F81" authorityName="Hayata" authorityYear="1913" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Ericaceae" genus="Rhododendron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rhododendron leptosanthum" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="leptosanthum">
<emphasis id="93D7368876C380213C143A273D3FA9AE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Rhododendron leptosanthum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hayata (
<taxonomicName id="5C0850E7F59098196CFF7499CB7BAF3B" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Ericaceae" genus="Rhododendron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="family">Ericaceae</taxonomicName>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="86CE4D8A1D307C89E4E6631410094011" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="32E0078BA5511AC9929E079B2743BE3B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="114BC56FB0B9F3BEFC8E257ACEF4809F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The first author, Mrs Hsueh Lee, and Mr Hou-Jay Chen found young larvae feeding on tender shoots (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="5C1A8EF3D9A0AE7E47D82A650740B47C" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Field photographs of Pyrrhalta houjayi sp. nov. on host plant A young larvae feeding on tender shoots B host plant blooming and sprouting at the same time in Tahsuehshan (大雪山) C flower buds with holes caused by larvae D Larva found inside the flower buds E one larva feeding on pedicels F adults." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545539" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">9A</figureCitation>
) April 1, 2009 in Lalashan, northern Taiwan. mature larvae started to burrow into soil and built underground chambers for pupation April 11. The newly eclosed adults emerged from soil April 28. The first author and Mr. Ta-Hsiang Lee found the host plants blooming and sprouting at the same time (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6A17A72DC79A74124EC2BF376655B84C" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Field photographs of Pyrrhalta houjayi sp. nov. on host plant A young larvae feeding on tender shoots B host plant blooming and sprouting at the same time in Tahsuehshan (大雪山) C flower buds with holes caused by larvae D Larva found inside the flower buds E one larva feeding on pedicels F adults." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545539" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">9B</figureCitation>
) April 21, 2010 in Tahsuehshan, central Taiwan. Many larvae were found inside flower buds with holes (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B33E17C4F61153778854FBCA5C2B74F8" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Field photographs of Pyrrhalta houjayi sp. nov. on host plant A young larvae feeding on tender shoots B host plant blooming and sprouting at the same time in Tahsuehshan (大雪山) C flower buds with holes caused by larvae D Larva found inside the flower buds E one larva feeding on pedicels F adults." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545539" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">9C, D</figureCitation>
). Some larvae preferred to feed on pedicels (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="CE9751E25F557258988A81E873360B0E" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Field photographs of Pyrrhalta houjayi sp. nov. on host plant A young larvae feeding on tender shoots B host plant blooming and sprouting at the same time in Tahsuehshan (大雪山) C flower buds with holes caused by larvae D Larva found inside the flower buds E one larva feeding on pedicels F adults." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545539" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">9E</figureCitation>
). Newly emerged adults appeared during late spring, into summer (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E26836D3C21B20E25039D4BA8F13A701" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Field photographs of Pyrrhalta houjayi sp. nov. on host plant A young larvae feeding on tender shoots B host plant blooming and sprouting at the same time in Tahsuehshan (大雪山) C flower buds with holes caused by larvae D Larva found inside the flower buds E one larva feeding on pedicels F adults." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545539" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">9F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
