<subSubSection id="D92BEBBF4D1225B0DCCD6CA706139651" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="89D7115414959584C3805CC6B04F6B1A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="506DF85E69260A490A510B5AA3B0F5EB" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">This new species is widespread at mid-altitudes (1,500-2,500 m) in Taiwan.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7E07BA1C510C8EFCA45FCD5A788934D0" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="F704550FF13164DC954506D944FD10B5" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2042CCFD1EC7DF78BF66FFA1141E2B34" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Dedicated to Mrs Su-Fang Yu who was the first member of TCRT to collect specimens of this new species and rear them successfully from eggs to adults.</paragraph>
